- implanter tous les flags, qui sont pour le moment superbement ignores.
J'ai quand meme laisse deux macros SIZ et SIZE selon qu'on affecte ou non.

- for the rounding modes, replace 'unsigned char' by 'int' which is usually
  preferred (also take care between 'char' and 'unsigned char')

- create a type 'mpfr_prec' (easier to change to unsigned long long if
	necessary)

- for all instructions that call malloc/realloc/etc, handle error cases
  (for example return an int indicating if an error occurred)

- in all functions that do rounding, return an int indicating if the result
  is exact (i.e. no bit was lost) or not (like in mpfr_div_ui)

- rename mpfr_log2 into mpfr_const_log2 (since log2 exists in C,
	mpfr_log2 should give the logarithm in base 2 of a number)
  and mpfr_pi into mpfr_const_pi
